Detailed Course Curriculum for Back-End Training

1. Ruby
    1. Introduction
    2. Simple Examples
    3. Strings
    4. Regular Expressions
    5. Arrays
    6. Control Structures
    7. Iterators
    8. Simple Examples.
    9. Methods
    10. Classes
    11. Inheritence
    12. Modules
    13. Variables
        1. Global Variables
        2. Instance Variables
        3. Local Variables
        4. Class Variables
    14. Accessors
    15. Objects

2.  Database (Postgres)
    1. Introduction
    2. Features
    3. Comparisons with other databases
    4. SQL Languages
        1. SQL syntax
        2. Data Definition
        3. Data Manipulation
        4. Datatypes
        5. Functions and Operators
    5. Server Administration
        1. Server Configuration
        2. Client authentication
        3. Manage Databases
        4. Manage Roles

3.  ActiveRecord
    1. Introduction
    2. Introduction to ORM
    3. Creating ActiveRecord Models
    4. CRUD Operations
    5. Validations
    6. ActiveRecord Callbacks
    7. Migrations

4. Rails
    1. Introduction
    2. MVC
        1. Models
        2. Views
            1. Layouts and Rendering
            2. Action View Form Helpers
        3. Controllers
            1. Routing
    3. Rails Internationalization (I18n)
    4. Action Mailer
    5. Configuring Rails Application
    6. Assets

5. Rails-API
    1. Introduction
    2. HTTP Methods
    3. Interacting using POSTMAN
    4. Creating JSON Requests.
    5. Difference between JSON and XML
    6. Serialization